I think this is a great event and I like so many that are coming in defense of Ak'Anon.  If this was real life our characters could stand before the entrance and try to stop Apep and his goons coming in.  But we can't do this unless we all duel.  Now I don't know but all of us going around like a bunch of Samurai challenging and dueling, that doesn't seem right to me.  If my character was going to dance with Apep I'd hire about 8 Ogres to mug him and about 30 bowmen to wack anyone trying to aid him (lots of beer money that day).  Is it possible, and I am sure someone that posts here can give me this answer (smirk)...can Verant for a couple hours on a specific day make Steamfont and Ak'Anon pvp.  That way those who want to raid, raid.  Those who want to defend, defend.  And no one needs take off their Guild tag.  Just warn the newbies a couple days before and when the time runs out no more pvp.  I'm sure some of those computer brainiac guys could make the server do this.  Just a thought.<br>
